China Steel, Formosa Petrochemical, TSMC: Taiwan Stocks Preview

-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 
2011-08-24T00:05:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/china-steel-formosa-petrochemical-tsmc-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of last close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index advanced 237.64, or 3.3 percent, to
7,550.23.  Cheng Uei Precision Industry Co. (2392 TT): The company
plans to increase the number of its “Studio A” stores selling
Apple Inc. products by the end of next year, the Economic Daily
News reported today, citing company officials it didn’t
identify. The stock jumped 6.9 percent to NT$80.70.  China Steel Corp. (2002)  (2002 TT): Taiwan’s largest steelmaker
said second-quarter profit declined 32 percent after it failed
to pass on increased costs. Net income declined to NT$8.67
billion ($299 million) in the three months ended June 30, from
NT$12.8 billion a year earlier, according to figures derived
from first-half earnings released by the Kaohsiung-based mill
yesterday. The stock rose 1.4 percent to NT$29.70.  Formosa Petrochemical Corp. (6505)  (6505 TT): Taiwan’s only
publicly traded oil refiner reported first-half net income of
NT$27.2 billion, the company said in a statement to the local
stock exchange yesterday. That was higher than NT$21.2 billion
reported a year earlier, according to a previous filing. The
stock added 5.9 percent to NT$84.70.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (2330 TT): It
expects orders to rebound next quarter driven by communications
and mobile phone chips, the Commercial Times reported today,
citing an internal company meeting held last week. The stock of
the world’s largest contract chipmaker rallied 2.8 percent to
NT$66.80.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adela Lin in Taipei at 
